Case was raised in a very conservative & controlled environment, which seemed to only add to Case’s rebellious attitude. Constantly fighting for a voice of her own Case found herself in and out of trouble; until finally being expelled from her high school.
At the age of 18 Case left home & moved to Los Angeles where she was living out of her 93’ Pontiac Bonneville in high hopes to pursue her career in the music industry. It was then that Case met singer/songwriter Ajay Marshall who took Case under his wing and brought her into the studio to record for the very first time. Case and Marshall worked together for the next couple years honing in on Case’s skills as a singer and a songwriter.
After releasing an acoustic demo online and playing a few local shows, Case decided that she wanted to reach an even bigger audience to drive to her original music by posting cover videos online.
